Ukrainian troops free three villages in Donetsk region, fighting for Lysychansk - Jul. 23, 2014
“The Ukrainian flag was raised over local administrations… Ukrainian troops continue to surround Donetsk from all sides,” the document said.
“Battles are now being held in Lysychansk [in Luhansk region],” the Defense Ministry said.
The villages of Karlivka, Netailove and Pervomaiske are north-west of Donetsk in close proximity to the regional center. Lysychansk forms the single Lysychansk-Severodonetsk metropolitan area together with Severodonetsk and Rubizhne.